tial tests: there’s a `DiscriminatorLookupTest` setup with `CodecRegistry` and `Animal` class. I'll check if the discriminator on `Animal` allows for `Dog`, which extends it. I’m concerned about whether `Dog` inherits the discriminator annotation. This automatic class model should collect annotations, so maybe it works for `Dog` as well. I need to investigate this.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating class discrimination**\\n\\nI'm pondering whether the `Dog` class name could cause issues if it contains a \\\"$\\\" for nested classes, since the discriminator would then have that symbol too. The test input shouldn't include versioning with a dollar sign in its name. I’m wondering if using `Dog.class.getName()` is safe, despite the potential for the `$` symbol. For dynamic access, using `Class.forName()` should still work. I’m also curious about whether native images properly include test classes and how reflection config plays into this. Will all classes be reachable?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing nested class accessibility**\\n\\nI’m considering whether the native image includes test classes accessible through JUnit. If the `Dog` class is nested, it might be reachable due to the compile reference that creates the string. I think the `Dog` class is likely included because the test code references `Dog.class.getName()` directly. However, since the target dynamic access report focuses only on library calls, using `Class.forName()` with the test class name seems okay, as I don’t think it requires reflection directly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_oJVHIjA5pnY1vkwbD9GZOxBg|fc_0d6f805833b0d1280169f14bd1d868819fa8dc930b7a66ee4f", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mongodb/bson/4.11.1/src/test/java/org_mongodb/bson/DiscriminatorLookupTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_mongodb.bson;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\nimport static org.bson.codecs.configuration.CodecRegistries.fromProviders;\nimport static org.bson.codecs.configuration.CodecRegistries.fromRegistries;\n\nimport org.bson.BsonDocument;\nimport org.bson.BsonDocumentReader;\nimport org.bson.BsonString;\nimport org.bson.codecs.Codec;\nimport org.bson.codecs.DecoderContext;\nimport org.bson.codecs.ValueCodecProvider;\nimport org.bson.codecs.configuration.CodecRegistry;\nimport org.bson.codecs.pojo.PojoCodecProvider;\nimport org.bson.codecs.pojo.annotations.BsonDiscriminator;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class DiscriminatorLookupTest {\n    private static final CodecRegistry CODEC_REGISTRY = fromRegistries(\n            fromProviders(new ValueCodecProvider()),\n            fromProviders(PojoCodecProvider.builder().automatic(true).build()));\n\n    @Test\n    void decodesPojoUsingFullyQualifiedDiscriminatorClassName() {\n        BsonDocument document = new BsonDocument();\n        document.append(\"_t\", new BsonString(DiscriminatorDog.class.getName()));\n        document.append(\"name\", new BsonString(\"Barkley\"));\n        document.append(\"favoriteTrick\", new BsonString(\"roll over\"));\n\n        DiscriminatorAnimal decoded = decode(document, DiscriminatorAnimal.class);\n\n        assertThat(decoded).isInstanceOf(DiscriminatorDog.class);\n        DiscriminatorDog dog = (DiscriminatorDog) decoded;\n        assertThat(dog.getName()).isEqualTo(\"Barkley\");\n        assertThat(dog.getFavoriteTrick()).isEqualTo(\"roll over\");\n    }\n\n    private static <T> T decode(BsonDocument document, Class<T> type) {\n        Codec<T> codec = CODEC_REGISTRY.get(type);\n        return codec.decode(new BsonDocumentReader(document), DecoderContext.builder().build());\n    }\n\n    @BsonDiscriminator\n    public static class DiscriminatorAnimal {\n        private String name;\n\n        public DiscriminatorAnimal() {\n        }\n\n        public String getName() {\n            return name;\n        }\n\n        public void setName(String name) {\n            this.name = name;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class DiscriminatorDog extends DiscriminatorAnimal {\n        private String favoriteTrick;\n\n        public DiscriminatorDog() {\n        }\n\n        public String getFavoriteTrick() {\n            return favoriteTrick;\n        }\n\n        public void setFavoriteTrick(String favoriteTrick) {\n            this.favoriteTrick = favoriteTrick;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/org.mongodb/bson/4.11.1/src/test/java/org_mongodb/bson/DiscriminatorLookupTest.java\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_mongodb.bson;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\nimport static org.bson.codecs.configuration.CodecRegistries.fromProviders;\\nimport static org.bson.codecs.configuration.CodecRegistries.fromRegistries;\\n\\nimport org.bson.BsonDocument;\\nimport org.bson.BsonDocumentReader;\\nimport org.bson.BsonString;\\nimport org.bson.codecs.Codec;\\nimport org.bson.codecs.DecoderContext;\\nimport org.bson.codecs.ValueCodecProvider;\\nimport org.bson.codecs.configuration.CodecRegistry;\\nimport org.bson.codecs.pojo.PojoCodecProvider;\\nimport org.bson.codecs.pojo.annotations.BsonDiscriminator;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\n\\npublic class DiscriminatorLookupTest {\\n    private static final CodecRegistry CODEC_REGISTRY = fromRegistries(\\n            fromProviders(new ValueCodecProvider()),\\n            fromProviders(PojoCodecProvider.builder().automatic(true).build()));\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void decodesPojoUsingFullyQualifiedDiscriminatorClassName() {\\n        BsonDocument document = new BsonDocument();\\n        document.append(\\\"_t\\\", new BsonString(DiscriminatorDog.class.getName()));\\n        document.append(\\\"name\\\", new BsonString(\\\"Barkley\\\"));\\n        document.append(\\\"favoriteTrick\\\", new BsonString(\\\"roll over\\\"));\\n\\n        DiscriminatorAnimal decoded = decode(document, DiscriminatorAnimal.class);\\n\\n        assertThat(decoded).isInstanceOf(DiscriminatorDog.class);\\n        DiscriminatorDog dog = (DiscriminatorDog) decoded;\\n        assertThat(dog.getName()).isEqualTo(\\\"Barkley\\\");\\n        assertThat(dog.getFavoriteTrick()).isEqualTo(\\\"roll over\\\");\\n    }\\n\\n    private static <T> T decode(BsonDocument document, Class<T> type) {\\n        Codec<T> codec = CODEC_REGISTRY.get(type);\\n        return codec.decode(new BsonDocumentReader(document), DecoderContext.builder().build());\\n    }\\n\\n    @BsonDiscriminator\\n    public static class DiscriminatorAnimal {\\n        private String name;\\n\\n        public DiscriminatorAnimal() {\\n        }\\n\\n        public String getName() {\\n            return name;\\n        }\\n\\n        public void setName(String name) {\\n            this.name = name;\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    public static class DiscriminatorDog extends DiscriminatorAnimal {\\n        private String favoriteTrick;\\n\\n        public DiscriminatorDog() {\\n        }\\n\\n        public String getFavoriteTrick() {\\n            return favoriteTrick;\\n        }\\n\\n        public void setFavoriteTrick(String favoriteTrick) {\\n            this.favoriteTrick = favoriteTrick;\\n        }\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2686, "output": 1435, "cacheRead": 49664, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 53785, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777421250122, "responseId": "resp_0d6f805833b0d1280169f14bc2c65c819f9619a